Kristen Stewart Shares NSFW Meaning Behind Her New Tattoo ‚Äî And It's Not What You Think The ‚ÄúTwilight‚Äù actor marked her directorial debut with some daring new ink at France's Cannes Film Festival. By Curtis M. Wong Senior Culture Reporter, HuffPost May 21, 2025, 02:00 PM EDT LEAVE A COMMENT LOADING ERROR LOADING Kristen Stewart is celebrating the debut of her first-ever directorial feature with some fresh ink. The ‚ÄúTwilight‚Äù actor attended France‚Äôs Cannes Film Festival where her new film, ‚Äú The Chronology of Water ,‚Äù held its world premiere last week. She walked the red carpet in an all-white Chanel suit with trouser shorts in which her new tattoo, which reads ‚ÄúMINE‚Äù in all capital letters and is positioned on her right thigh, was visible. Kristen Stewart is making her directorial feature debut with "The Chronology of Water," which premiered at France's Cannes Film Festival last week. Mondadori Portfolio via Getty Images Advertisement Many fans were quick to assume that the tattoo was an homage to Taylor Swift ‚Äôs ‚Äú Guilty as Sin? ‚Äù The song, which appears on Swift‚Äôs 2024 album ‚Äú The Tortured Poets Department ‚Äù and is rumored to have been inspired by her brief romance with The 1975 musician Matty Healy , features the lyric: ‚ÄúWhat if he‚Äôs written ‚Äòmine‚Äô on my upper thigh, only in my mind?‚Äù But in an interview with New York Magazine‚Äôs Vulture blog , Stewart revealed that the new tattoo ‚Äï which members of the movie‚Äôs film crew also received ‚Äï is a wink at an especially titillating scene in ‚ÄúThe Chronology of Water.‚Äù Stewart's new thigh tattoo, which reads "MINE" in capital letters, was visible beneath her trouser shorts. Lyvans Boolaky via Getty Images Advertisement ‚ÄúThe coolest song in the movie is when she comes on her hand, smells it, wipes it on her fucking bicep, and goes, ‚ÄòI didn‚Äôt know a girl body could do that. Shoot come,‚Äô‚Äù she explained. ‚ÄúAnd then this song comes on and it goes, ‚ÄòMine, mine, mine, mine.‚Äô And it‚Äôs just fucking mine.‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Chronology of Water‚Äù is an adaptation of Lidia Yuknavitch‚Äôs 2011 memoir of the same name. It follows Yuknavitch (played by British actor Imogen Poots ), who enrolls in a Texas college on a swimming scholarship. Her dreams of Olympic glory, however, are dashed when she begins dabbling in drug and alcohol use, though she later finds her true calling as a writer, a teacher and a mother. 20 Years Of Free Journalism Your Support Fuels Our Mission Your Support Fuels Our Mission For two decades, HuffPost has been fearless, unflinching, and relentless in pursuit of the truth. Stephane Cardinale - Corbis via Getty Images Advertisement Only time will tell if ‚ÄúThe Chronology of Water,‚Äù which also stars Jim Belushi, Thora Birch and Michael Epp, succeeds in establishing Stewart as a filmmaker in her own right. Speaking to The Hollywood Reporter last week , the Oscar nominee said the movie that is being screened at Cannes is just her ‚Äúfirst draft,‚Äù and that she hoped to refine it before it hits the big screen in a wider release. ‚ÄúWe barely finished this movie. Album: Dangerous And Moving ( 2005 ) Charted: 8 License This Song Ó†Ü lyrics Songfacts¬Æ: This song is about two girls who stick up for each other when either of them are in trouble. >> Suggestion credit : Chris - La Porte, IN Dangerous And Moving was t.A.T.u.'s second album, coming three years after their hit " All The Things She Said ." By the time this was released, the female duo was no longer being portrayed as lesbians, which added to their credibility but cost them dearly in media coverage. One of the singers, Julia Volkova, had a child before this song was released. This song was written by Billy Steinberg, Josh Alexander, and Jessica and Lisa Origliasso. The Origliasso's are Australian twins who record as The Veronicas. Steinberg is a prominent lyricist who, along with Tom Kelly, has written many hit songs, including the Bangles " Eternal Flame " and Cyndi Lauper's " True Colors ." >> Suggestion credit : Elizabeth - Old Town, ME More songs from t.A.T.u. It operates as a Provider of an online marketplace for tattoo designs . Tattoodo has raised $24.2M in funding from investors like Threadless , Seed Capital and Nordic Eye , with a current valuation of $70.6M . Company Details Provider of an online marketplace for tattoo designs. The platform allows designers to showcase and sell their tattoo designs. Enables clients to get custom designs by describing their idea and then receiving designs based on their choice. It is available on iOS and Android platforms.
